The 16-year-old victim from Port Elizabeth had while playing beach ball with friends apparently disappeared under water after slipping into a hole.National Sea Rescue Institute (NSRI) station commander Rieghard Janse van Rensburg said that six NSRI rescue swimmers and two Kouga Municipal lifeguards had formed a sweeping-line free-dive search and that during the search the body of the teenager was located and recovered. Paramedics declared the teenager deceased and the body has been taken into the care of the Forensic Pathology Services he added.